Catalyst-View-Thumbnail-Simple version 0.0008
===========================================

This module is a View class for Catalyst that will simply and
efficiently create thumbnails or `scaled' versions of images.

See `perldoc Catalyst::View::Thumbnail::Simple' for usage information.

INSTALLATION

To install this module type the following:

   perl Makefile.PL
   make
   make test
   make install

DEPENDENCIES

This module requires these other modules and libraries:

  Catalyst::View
  Imager
  Image::Info

Note that Imager requires several libraries (e.g. libpng, libjpeg) for
the ability to read some image file types. If you are unsure if you
have these dependencies installed, type the following in your command
shell to reveal what image types your version of Imager can currently
read:

  perl -MImager -e 'print join(q{, }, Imager->read_types) . qq{\n}'

See the Imager perldocs for more information on image formats.

